    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skin on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into thin discs</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-pork-and-beef-mince-ragu-with-carrot-mash/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potato </strong>and<strong> carrot discs</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-pork-and-beef-mince-ragu-with-carrot-mash/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the potato and carrot are cooking, peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-pork-and-beef-mince-ragu-with-carrot-mash/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further</p><p>Increase the heat to high and add your <strong>pork &</strong> <strong>beef mince</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-pork-and-beef-mince-ragu-with-carrot-mash/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail and chop your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into quarters lengthways, then slice finely</p><p>Once the mince has browned, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>courgette</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min further or until the courgette has started to soften</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-pork-and-beef-mince-ragu-with-carrot-mash/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> beef stock mix </strong>and <strong>harissa </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>harissa stock</strong></p><p>Once the courgette has softened, add the <strong>harissa stock</strong> and your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and cook for 10-12 min or until the sauce has thickened to a bolognese-like consistency and the meat is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>harissa pork & beef mince rag\u00f9</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-pork-and-beef-mince-ragu-with-carrot-mash/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the pork & beef rag\u00f9 is cooking, strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them finely, discard the stems</p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Return the <strong>drained potato and carrot </strong>to a low heat<strong> </strong>with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>and<strong> mint </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Mash until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>herby yoghurt & carrot mash</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/harissa-pork-and-beef-mince-ragu-with-carrot-mash/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>harissa pork & beef mince rag\u00f9 </strong>with the<strong> herby yoghurt & carrot mash </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle over the<strong> remaining natural yoghurt </strong>and sprinkle over the<strong> remaining chopped parsley </strong>and<strong> mint</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
